AGI - "I am not afraid of the idea of the referendum and I do not consider it a referendum on me. I consider it a referendum on the future of Italy." The President of the Council, Giorgia Meloni>, at 'In half an hour', clarifies that it will not be resigned in the event of a rejection of the constitutional reform which introduces the premiership >: "If the reform does not pass it will mean that the Italians" do not approve it. "I arrive at the end of my five years and ask the Italians to be judged. On the rest ... They are hopes from the left", he continued during an interview that covered most of the hottest dossiers, from Ukraine to the Middle East, from the Toti case to the European elections.&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;
So what did you mean, "O go or kick it"? "'It was because they asked me 'think it might be dangerous, why can it bring you problems if the reform does not pass?'. Who cares? If the reform does not pass it will mean that the Italians will not have shared it. No, look, we're not getting it. I arrive at the end of my five years and it is there that I will ask the Italians to be judged, when I finish my work", he emphasized.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
The accusations from the opposition of unavailability to dialogue are rejected to the sender: "I don't think that the call for dialogue goes to me because I have already proven to be available to dialogue. I remember leaving from a proposal of semi-presidency to French. I consulted the political forces and came to another reform that went to meet what political forces asked. The first of these demands was the role of the head of the state. It is a figure whose authority is recognized by all and therefore we have not touched the role of the head of the state". &nbsp;
&nbsp;
With regard to the Albanian agreement on migrants, which is also the subject of controversy, the Prime Minister has assured that "forward, and it will be operational not very much. It will work and will do as a starter by similar others. It's a project we want to do for good." "Left members criticized us to make Guantanamo in Albania, now criticize us for the alleged delays," he continued, I want to thank Edi Rama."
On the war in Ukraine many objectionable statements
An inevitable passage on the <a href="https://www.agi.it/estero/news/2024-05-25/apport-stoltenberg-use-Ukraine-russia-26520697/"> Statements </a> of the Secretary-General of NATO, Jens Stoltenberg>, who urged allies to allow Kiev to use the weapons provided for targets in Russian territory. "I do not know why Stoltenberg says something like this. I think we have to be very careful. NATO must maintain its firmness."
&nbsp;
"There have been a lot of statements in recent months that seemed questionable to me," he continued, citing the phrases of Emmanuel Macron on the sending of land troops, "I recommend greater caution". &nbsp;
Israel also respects international law
Speaking of the other major international crisis in progress, the Gaza war, Meloni, which yesterday met the Palestinian homologue Mohammad Mustafa, believes &nbsp; "that the need to respect international law must be reiterated against Israel." "What I see that Israel is likely to fit exactly into the trap that the fundamentalists had packaged - it has observed - that trap was forcing Israel to a reprisal on the territory of the house that was very strong because the strategy of fundamentalism is historically to isolate Israel." "This is happening on the international level, it is happening in our public opinions and I believe that this is why we must reiterate, even towards Israel, the need to respect international law," said Meloni, who dictated "disappearance" by the absence of empathy that has been and is on Israeli civilian victims. This tells a latent anti-Semitism that is coming out and is worrying"
&nbsp;
"We must continue to work for a ceasefire for the release of all hostages, I think we must prevent an Israeli attack on Rafah. I think we must strengthen the Palestinian national authority: This is what I said yesterday to the Palestinian prime minister, it is a fundamental step if we want to build a stable and lasting perspective, of peace also for the Middle East. I think Italy must be very proud of the work it has done in recent months on the humanitarian support plan," he continued, "I also think that we must not wait to build a stable structural solution. It would be a mistake if we began to talk about the 'two peoples two states' when the crisis ended - it has emphasized the premier -. I think one of the ways to end the crisis is to start talking about it right away. And on this Italy is having a role. And I think Europe can play a role on this."
<h2> Toti case? "Only he knows the truth"</h2>
Another delicate chapter is what concerns the president of the Liguria Region, Giovanni Toti, accused of corruption. Would your resignation be appropriate? "I believe that only John Toti is in the position to answer this question, because only he knows the truth. I think he's in a position to assess what's best for the citizens of his region." &nbsp;
&nbsp;
"I had no way to talk to Giovanni Toti and it is difficult to get an idea done on this story. For the future I'd like to," and it's for everyone, "that between when there's a request for precautionary measures and when performed they didn't spend months. Don't wait for election campaigns," he added.
&nbsp;
"I think this committee and this Europe have been very wrong. It's not like I say it in Italy, I say it in Europe." The President of the Council Giorgia Meloni said this at 'In half'orà, denying that there are changes in the line in Europe. "I have an institutional collaboration with Ursula von der Leyen," he added. "From times Ursula von der Leyen seemed more pragmatic than his majority," he replied to those who asked her if she recently "molated" the president of the EU commission, running for a second term.
<h2>"Left to opposition also in Europe"</h2>
Finally, the European elections. As far as a right-hand extension of a new driving majority Ppe?&nbsp;&nbsp; "I'm not used to presentability licenses," Meloni said, "my main goal is to try to build a centre-right majority and send the left to the opposition in Europe," he said, "I think that the rainbow majority produce is compromised. We are not in a historical season in which we can afford a Europe with compromises to the downfall. People who are part of the majority decide it. I am not willing to make a majority with the left, all the rest is seen."&nbsp;
&nbsp;
And the debate on Europe inevitably implies that on the stability pact that "has a temporary phase of return, is sustainable on paper". "The better way to support public debt is to promote growth. We must continue to signal our productive world. We found a pretty disastrous situation. As for the cohesion funds 2014-20, of 120 billion, 47 had been spent: tell me if Italy can afford not to spend these resources", he continued.&nbsp; "On the card the disaster is on the 220 million euro hole for having renovated 4% of the houses. In any case, this government will do its best by concentrating resources on important things." &nbsp;
